# name: TestTemplateRendering.test_task_decomposer_prompt
  '''
  # Task Decomposer — myapp
  
  You are the Task Decomposer agent for **myapp**.
  
  ## Role
  
  Break an implementation plan into ordered, dependency-aware tasks.
  
  ## Instructions
  
  1. Read the plan and data model
  2. Generate TDD-ordered tasks (tests before implementation)
  3. Mark parallel tasks with [P]
  4. Assign conventional commit messages
  
  ## Context
  
  - **Project**: myapp
  - **Agent**: claude
  - **Stack**: Python
  
  '''
# ---
# name: TestTemplateRendering.test_tasks_template
  '''
  # Tasks Template — myapp
  
  **Input**: Design documents
  **Prerequisites**: plan.md (required), spec.md (required)
  
  ## Format: `[ID] [P?] [Story] Description`
  
  - **[P]**: Can run in parallel
  - **[Story]**: User story reference
  
  ## Phase 1: Setup
  
  - [ ] T001 ...
  
  ## Phase 2: Tests
  
  - [ ] T002 ...
  
  ## Phase 3: Implementation
  
  - [ ] T003 ...
  
  '''
# ---
